00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:42,520
No wonder he hasn't
got a girlfriend.

243
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:49,479
Thing is, Baz, splitting
up consignments

244
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:53,040
ain't doing us any favours, we need
someone who can take the lot.

245
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:56,200
I'm seeing this German
geezer later on,

246
00:14:56,201 --> 00:14:58,480
he says he can take
whatever we've got.

247
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:06,959
I ain't trying to pull a fast one,

248
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:11,599
but a Troy ounce of gold was 875
quid when I woke up this morning.

249
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:14,359
Now, unless you know
something I don't,

250
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:16,359
why would I get less than that?

251
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:19,359
We'll give you 875 for
your domestic business,

252
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:25,159
but we are aware that sometimes
your sources are not always...

253
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:26,279
Legitimate?

254
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:28,719
So, if you want to use us

255
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:31,599
but you don't want us to ask,
"where is it coming from?"

256
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,719
Then we like to pay
a little less, ja?

257
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:35,239
Yeah, yeah.

258
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:38,759
So, uh...How much can you take?

259
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:41,319
We have no upper limit.

260
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:44,199
- And payment?
- What's your preference?

261
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:46,719
Cash.

262
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:50,599
The money laundering laws
are very stringent in Germany.

263
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:54,959
- Bankers draft or direct transfers.
- Agreed.

264
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:58,479
We have a 2m euro ceiling
on direct transfers.

265
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:01,240
Looks like you've found
your UK supplier.

266
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:26,039
You see, melting down trinkets sent
in by wrinklies feeling the pinch

267
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:29,199
ain't going to build my new pool,
is it, Barry? Let's be honest.

268
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,799
And the dealers are squeezing
all the margins, so...

269
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:34,479
The krauts have agreed to
take whatever we can supply,

270
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,760
no upper limit.

271
00:16:35,761 --> 00:16:38,559
So, bish bosh, open up the
till, keep the change.

272
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:39,840
So, when do we start, boss?

273
00:16:39,841 --> 00:16:42,799
I told him I'd send him his first
shipment at the end of next week.

274
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,879
There's a couple of the
lads planning jobs.

275
00:16:44,880 --> 00:16:48,999
A cargo terminal at Stansted
and an arab bank in Kensington.

276
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,119
But they're a few weeks away,
so, if there's no hooky gold about,

277
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:54,080
let's get a few more
press ads running.

278
00:16:54,081 --> 00:16:57,759
Knitting magazines, something
to terrify the bingo squad,

279
00:16:57,760 --> 00:17:01,239
"recession to bite deep,
fuel prices to soar.

280
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:04,839
"The cost of cardigans and blue
rinses to go through the roof.

281
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:08,359
"What use is your wedding ring
if you can't turn the heating on?"

282
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:11,360
Maybe do a special offer for widows!

283
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:16,079
I like what you did there, Baz.

284
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:19,879
Yeah. And then let's start with the
housewives, make 'em feel guilty

285
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:22,959
about their kids not having
the latest video games

286
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:25,679
while they're still
dripping in gold.

287
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:28,479
Do some photos of kids...Crying.

288
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:31,199
Right, get on with it!
I'm on it, boss!

289
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,599
Big push, Baz, ok?

290
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,760
Shania?

291
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,959
Sean, what have you got?

292
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,880
Well, according to his pa,
he's single,

293
00:17:43,881 --> 00:17:46,320
in between girlfriends,
which is his usual state,

294
00:17:46,321 --> 00:17:49,119
he's not a member of any clubs,
only drinks champagne,

295
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:52,239
preferably bollinger, hates dogs,
women in flat shoes

296
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:55,559
and bread-and-butter pudding.
And his lucky number's five.

297
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:58,319
So... supports Tottenham,
never goes to live matches,

298
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:01,799
his favourite singers are Michael
Buble, Shirley Bassey and Madonna.

299
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:03,999
His favourite film
is saving private Ryan.

300
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,679
Plays paintball on the weekend.

301
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:08,079
Favourite colour's gold.
On the rare occasion

302
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:10,959
he does go to a fancy dress party
he goes as auric goldfinger,

303
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:14,079
the bloke from the bond film,
but no-one ever knows who he is.

304
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:17,160
Oh, and he's got a parrot
named Goldie.

305
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:21,259
Ok. Emma?

306
00:18:21,260 --> 00:18:24,359
He's listed as a director
of 11 companies, all gold-related,

307
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:27,359
with a combined
turnover of £3m,

308
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:29,239
so, I think we can say
he's above the poverty line.

309
00:18:29,540 --> 00:18:32,339
- Props?
- Everything's in place, ready to go.

310
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:33,619
And what about our bait?

311
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:36,320
Ah, our bait...

312
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:41,140
..Looks a little something like...

313
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:45,359
..This.

314
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:46,840
Ooh...

315
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,439
Wow.
Is that real?

316
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:52,279
Oh, yes.

317
00:18:52,280 --> 00:18:53,879
32 grand's worth,
give or take.

318
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:56,999
It's rented, so it has to go back
in one piece when we're done.

319
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,679
That should get his attention.

320
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:01,599
Oh... he's got a four o'clock
meeting out in the sticks.

321
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:04,159
Then let's bring him in.

322
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:05,999
(Music blares)

323
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,360
(He sings tunelessly)

324
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,880
(Thud of an impact)

325
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:29,520
Hngh...?!

326
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,040
- Do you want to die?
- No.

327
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:35,319
In about 15 seconds, six blokes
are going to come out of the woods.

328
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:38,159
They'll kill me first,
then shoot you just for fun.

329
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:42,679
So, get in the car and drive.

330
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:44,160
Now!

331
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:58,000
He's in.

332
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:13,599
They jumped me on the way back
from their so-called dealers.

333
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:15,319
It must have been a setup.

334
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:17,919
No, no, no, I flagged a ride.

335
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:20,399
No, he's a civilian, it's all right.

336
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:23,320
I'll be back in an hour,
you just sit tight.

337
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:32,159
Ok, look, I'm sorry
to drag you into this,

338
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:35,519
but I was up shit creek and you
just happened to be there.

339
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:36,640
You saved my life.

340
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:40,040
I owe you one.

341
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:43,359
Who was after you?

342
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:45,600
Greedy bastards, that's who.

343
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:51,000
But you got me out and that takes
guts. You ever been in the forces?

344
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:53,719
No. I thought about the ta once.

345
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:56,560
Oh, you should do it.
Yeah? Yeah.

346
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:04,480
Is that what I think it was?

347
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:08,239
What if it was?

348
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:10,160
I heard you on the phone,
about the dealer.

349
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:14,399
- Am I going to have trouble
with you, son? - No, no.

350
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,359
The thing is, that's what I do.

351
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:17,679
What?

352
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:19,200
I'm a gold dealer.

353
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:24,040
Yeah, yeah, course you are.

354
00:21:24,041 --> 00:21:29,159
Listen, thanks for the ride,
sorry for the inconvenience.

355
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:31,560
No! No, look, look.
Here's my card.

356
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:37,680
If you got something to sell,
I can find a buyer.

357
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:00,219
You think it worked?

358
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:03,739
Well, that's the thing about greed.
It's very predictable.

359
00:22:03,740 --> 00:22:05,819
Great.

360
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:10,719
Sean, can you get us into
his offices tomorrow morning?

361
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,799
Yeah, I'll call Shania,
my new best friend.

362
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,920
Look, we've got to do something
about Eddie.

363
00:22:14,979 --> 00:22:16,179
Yeah, I said that.

364
00:22:17,180 --> 00:22:21,060
There we go.
Enjoy.

365
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:26,799
- We need to do something about Eddie.
- I have an idea. Oh, yeah?

366
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,599
I'm going to call in a favour.

367
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:31,359
(Phone rings)

368
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:33,119
Hello, Eddie's bar.

369
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:35,159
- It's Ian rush here.
- 'What?'

370
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:38,159
do me a favour, that's pathetic.
You don't even sound like him.

371
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:41,519
Hey, listen, I don't know who
you are, but you can tell that lot

372
00:22:41,520 --> 00:22:44,320
that I'm not as stupid as they
think I am, all right? Ya f...

373
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,800
Nice try, but he
didn't believe us.

374
00:22:49,801 --> 00:22:53,599
Ok. Albert, Emma.
See if you can work on him.

375
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:56,359
Hey, why me? I didn't draw
ears on his football hero!

376
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:58,299
He's got a soft spot for you.
I'm not sleeping

377
00:22:58,300 --> 00:22:59,799
with him just so Ash can have a fry up.

378
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:02,139
- That's your trouble, ems.
You're selfish. - Not funny.

379
00:23:02,140 --> 00:23:05,359
Just tell him it was Albert.
He can apologise, end of.

380
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:07,719
- Oh, but why me?
- Oh, Mickey then.

381
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:11,719
We won't tell him it was Mickey, cos
he'll make Mickey's life a misery.

382
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,539
Albert, tell him it was Sean.
Hang on a minute!

383
00:23:13,540 --> 00:23:15,039
Sean, you're the youngest.

384
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:17,759
Well, if you grass me up,
I'm taking you all down with me.

385
00:23:17,760 --> 00:23:19,279
Aren't we forgetting something here?

386
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:21,279
It is Eddie we're talking about.

387
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:24,199
Ash is right, I'm sending
two premier league grifters

388
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:26,600
to deal with one barman,
it shouldn't be a contest.

389
00:23:26,601 --> 00:23:29,520
He's really stubborn, though.
You'll think of something.

390
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:37,520
Brass may be your best bet.

391
00:23:37,521 --> 00:23:39,679
It won't be cheap
but it will look the part

392
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:41,959
once it's melted down
and moulded into blocks.

393
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:44,239
Well, give us a ball park, Arnie.

394
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:48,000
Five grand if I get it back,
ten if I don't. Done.

395
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,080
Ok. What about this?

396
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:59,959
What do you need?
A different seal on it.

397
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:02,479
Well, I'll have to melt it down
so I can stamp it.

398
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:04,399
Can you do that?

399
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:06,760
If it's made of metal, Mickey,
I can do anything.

400
00:24:06,761 --> 00:24:08,880
(Ash sniggers)

401
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:13,519
Metal Mickey?

402
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:15,239
Never mind.

403
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:16,840
What seal do you need on it?

404
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:19,240
This one.

405
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:25,120
We'll see you at 8.30.

406
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:36,338
- I don't believe you.
- It's true.

407
00:24:36,339 --> 00:24:37,439
You wouldn't do that, Albert,

408
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:38,979
- you're just protecting someone.
- Eddie!

409
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:42,119
Why ask one of us to apologise if,
when we do, you don't believe us?

410
00:24:42,120 --> 00:24:44,719
- You're just taking me for a mug.
- No, we're not.

411
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,640
What about the fella
you got to phone up?

412
00:24:46,641 --> 00:24:49,759
- The one pretending to be Ian rush?
- No, it actually was Ian rush.

413
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:51,519
You're doing it again, treating me
like an idiot.

414
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,019
Eddie, you're impossible!

415
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:55,359
- And you're barred.
- Would it help if I slept with you?

416
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:56,679
- No.
- What?!

417
00:24:56,680 --> 00:25:00,199
Sorry, I panicked just then,
I meant to say yeah. Eddie!

418
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:03,559
Listen, I know he did it and
until he comes here in person,

419
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:06,839
apologises and says in front
of witnesses that liverpool FC

420
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:10,120
are better than west ham,
then you're staying barred.

421
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:15,319
It's not happening. I mean, the flaming
cheek of it, and I never did it.

422
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:17,759
He's convinced himself it was you and
there's no persuading him otherwise.

423
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:20,480
Come on, Ash, man up.
Take one for the team.

424
00:25:20,681 --> 00:25:21,239
No.

425
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:23,119
It'll take you 20 seconds,
how hard can it be?

426
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:24,019
I ain't done it.

427
00:25:24,020 --> 00:25:27,339
- You are as stubborn as each other.
- I didn't do anything!

428
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:28,699
Think of Eddie's breakfast.

429
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:32,199
Yeah, he's finally got
his fried bread right.

430
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:35,479
Crunchy crust, a bit
soggy in the middle.

431
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:35,780
No.

432
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:39,240
I'd rather starve.

433
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:54,479
Thanks.

434
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:57,239
His diary's full but he's
got a gap in ten minutes...

435
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:58,519
Right.

436
00:25:58,520 --> 00:25:59,679
Morning.

437
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:00,219
We set?

438
00:26:00,220 --> 00:26:01,960
Yeah, if you lose it, I'm
stopping it out your wages.

439
00:26:04,840 --> 00:26:06,080
Wish me luck.

440
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:19,560
You gave this to a friend
of mine yesterday.

441
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:29,359
♪ oh, it feels so good

442
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:35,279
♪ to have you by my side
on a Sunday morning

443
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:39,919
♪ let's work together, baby, yeah. ♪

444
00:26:39,920 --> 00:26:44,200
Shania! Get yourself
a cup of tea, love.

445
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:51,079
You were kind enough
to give him a lift.

446
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:53,199
So what's on your mind?

447
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:55,279
Oh, I think you know
why I'm here.

448
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:57,560
Why don't you spell it out for me?

449
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:02,239
We have some merchandise. We're
having trouble finding a buyer.

450
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:05,879
Yeah, so I heard. That doesn't mean
you won't have to pay a decent price.

451
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:09,080
You'll have to let the dog
see the rabbit first.

452
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:30,439
Libyan?
Problem?

453
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,199
Not for me.

454
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:33,719
So you're interested, then?

455
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:38,239
It's what I do.
I'm a middle man.

456
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:43,159
I find two parties, each wanting
something the other has,

457
00:27:43,160 --> 00:27:46,159
and no way of coming together...

458
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:49,360
So, really, I'm a facilitator.

459
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:54,799
The bottom line is, I can find a
buyer for that with one phone call.

460
00:27:54,800 --> 00:28:00,199
- Good. - As long as you and your
boyfriend understand three things.

461
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:02,919
I'm assuming
he is your boyfriend?

462
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:04,360
Yes, he is.

463
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:07,480
That's what I thought.

464
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:10,679
- Where was I?
- Three things?

465
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:14,799
Yeah, right. I'm not a mug,
apart from the Libyan stamp,

466
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:18,560
all that drama yesterday tells me
it's obviously nicked, and, er...

467
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:24,879
I read the newspapers
like everybody else...

468
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:26,439
I know where this
has come from,

469
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:28,759
so the price I pay will
have to reflect that.

470
00:28:28,760 --> 00:28:30,519
Second.

471
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:35,599
My commission for negotiating this
deal is 20% at your end,

472
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,439
non-negotiable.

473
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:39,639
And third?

474
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:42,159
If you so much as think
about turning me over,

475
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:44,600
I know people who can track
you down and hurt you

476
00:28:44,601 --> 00:28:47,399
so much you'll be begging
them to finish you off.

477
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:49,480
I'll pass it on.

478
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:57,359
Once we've agreed a price, just
let us know where they need to go.

479
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:59,159
You mean there's more than one?

480
00:28:59,160 --> 00:29:00,480
Yes.

481
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:04,479
So... how many we
talking about exactly?

482
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:05,880
A hundred.

483
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:10,520
A hundred!
All the same as that one?

