485
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:17,959
You trying to tell me it was you...

486
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:20,159
If this is too big for you...

487
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:26,159
Oh, no... it might take more than
one phone call that's all...

488
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:28,519
Can I see them?
I don't know.

489
00:29:28,520 --> 00:29:30,640
My contacts don't like
being pissed about.

490
00:29:30,659 --> 00:29:32,759
If I don't see the goods,
I don't pick up the phone.

491
00:29:34,460 --> 00:29:35,820
It's your choice.

492
00:29:38,620 --> 00:29:40,979
The place where you
dropped our mutual friend,

493
00:29:40,980 --> 00:29:43,140
two o'clock this afternoon.

494
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:58,999
Holy shit.

495
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,039
I think we have a nibble.

496
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:02,200
Shania!

497
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,860
Get Heinz Zimmerman
on the phone.

498
00:30:06,899 --> 00:30:08,999
Then put the kettle on.

499
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:14,519
Will it stand up?

500
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:15,879
To what?

501
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:20,039
- Inspection.
- 100%. - Good.

502
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:22,320
As long as you don't get
within six feet.

503
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:25,199
This ain't chicken feed, Heinz,

504
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:28,839
we're talking 100 kilos of 24 carat,
this is a serious shipment.

505
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:30,159
When's it ready?

506
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:33,639
Well, we'll need to melt it down
and restamp, but I can...

507
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:36,879
I can do the paperwork...
The question is can you handle it?

508
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:39,360
You talk the talk buddy,
it's time to walk the walk.

509
00:30:39,361 --> 00:30:41,919
There's three mill's worth here,
are you in or are you out?

510
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:44,639
'Ok we have a deal,
I'll be there.'

511
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:45,840
good call, be in touch.

512
00:30:49,360 --> 00:30:50,919
♪ yo, mic check, mic check

513
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:55,239
♪ yeah here you go
nah, here, over here

514
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:56,840
♪ yeah, I heard he got
that hot new thing

515
00:30:56,841 --> 00:31:00,480
♪ oh-la-la-la. Yeah oh, yeah, yeah
turn it over. ♪

516
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:14,559
all right, babes?

517
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:17,320
Don't move or I'm gonna blow
your brains out, do you hear me?

518
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:41,599
Eddie's isn't the only bar
in London.

519
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:43,719
Maybe we should just find
somewhere else?

520
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:46,160
No, no, we'll find a way to sort it.

521
00:31:56,560 --> 00:32:01,080
Sorry about that, but we
can't disclose our location.

522
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:05,079
The British army have sent
a special ops unit to find us.

523
00:32:05,080 --> 00:32:07,520
Oh, well, fair enough then!

524
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:16,280
Oh, don't mind him.
He's just not the trusting type.

525
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:19,520
You all right then?

526
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,879
So, you think you
can get us a deal?

527
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:25,599
Yes, I do.

528
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:27,499
But it won't be easy, as I
told your lady friend here.

529
00:32:27,500 --> 00:32:31,139
- How much?
- Well, that's hard to say.

530
00:32:31,140 --> 00:32:33,140
- What was I telling you?
- Relax.

531
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:38,279
There's 100 bars.

532
00:32:38,280 --> 00:32:40,760
I looked it up, they're worth
about 30 grand each.

533
00:32:40,761 --> 00:32:43,839
If you buy 'em from the bank
of england, yeah, maybe...

534
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:46,240
But you won't get anything near
that, not for a shipment like this.

535
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:50,719
You can't move gold on without
paperwork. You need to, er,

536
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:54,759
melt it down, give it a new identity,
feed it back into the system.

537
00:32:54,760 --> 00:32:57,159
That takes time and money.

538
00:32:57,160 --> 00:33:00,039
You talking to us
about it not being easy?

539
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:05,039
Three months ago, we'd just done
a black ops stint in Libya,

540
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:08,199
dodging yank cruise missiles
and apache gun ships,

541
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:12,439
smuggling rebel supporters out of
tripoli before gaddafi got to them.

542
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:15,559
Gaddafi got his secret police
to move his stash of goodies

543
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:17,079
before the rebels arrived.

544
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:21,239
Artwork, cash... gold.

545
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:24,559
He died, we caught the gold truck
on the road out of tripoli.

546
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:27,799
And we...Relieved them of it.

547
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:30,959
Now we have not fought our
way across half of Africa,

548
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:35,439
carrying 100 kilos in gold bars and
then smuggled them into the uk,

549
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:38,559
just so some smarmy scumbag
civilian can try to rip us off.

550
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:40,519
Do you get me?

551
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:41,720
Back off, corporal.

552
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:45,239
(He laughs)

553
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:47,279
Yes, sir.

554
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:50,040
(He continues laughing)

555
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:54,879
How much?

556
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:57,398
I can get you half a million,
transferred into any account,

557
00:33:57,399 --> 00:33:59,699
you like, anywhere in
the world in 20 seconds.

558
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:01,199
I'd rather shoot him
where he stands.

559
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:03,399
You want to spend another
two weeks in here!?

560
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:06,479
We've been screwed
over twice now.

561
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:10,639
You won't get a better price,
I guarantee it. He's playing us.

562
00:34:10,640 --> 00:34:13,999
Half a million pounds
is a lot of money.

563
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,759
What about half a million,
but no commission?

564
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:20,098
You make what you
can when you move it on.

565
00:34:20,099 --> 00:34:24,099
- Commission is non-negotiable.
- Yeah? I say we negotiate.

566
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:26,879
All right! Ok!

567
00:34:26,880 --> 00:34:30,400
- Forget the commission. Heart of
gold, that's my trouble. - When?

568
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:39,880
I need to verify the shipment first.

569
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:55,120
I mean a sample,
check the purity.

570
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:12,999
What else?

571
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:16,320
Well, if it all checks out, I can get
this done in 24 hours. Bish bosh!

572
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:27,840
24 hours.

573
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:49,959
Well?

574
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:51,240
Bloody hell, boss.

575
00:35:51,241 --> 00:35:54,059
- It's top end, 24 carat.
- And?

576
00:35:54,060 --> 00:35:57,719
Well, it's Libyan government seal,
it's about as kosher as it gets.

577
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:59,059
What's it worth?

578
00:35:59,160 --> 00:36:05,739
Gold price this morning was up a
bit, so... just about £33,500?

579
00:36:06,240 --> 00:36:08,440
So 100 bars...?

580
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:14,800
Three million, three hundred
thousand, and change.

581
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:17,920
Hmm.

582
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:26,840
- Grub's up.
- Great!

583
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:30,279
The mark just called,
everything's set up for tomorrow.

584
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:31,579
We're just running
through a few things.

585
00:36:31,580 --> 00:36:38,559
- Oh, right. Er, two COD, Albert.
- Thank you. - And one for Mickey.

586
00:36:38,560 --> 00:36:41,840
Pie for me, haddock for ems...

587
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:46,319
- ..And a saveloy for Sean.
- Saveloy!

588
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:48,279
So, when did he phone?

589
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,959
About 20 minutes ago.

590
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:52,319
It'll be a pleasure to
take his money.

591
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:55,759
If this works, Albert was thinking
of giving some money to Vivienne,

592
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:59,039
you know, maybe send her on
a cruise or something. Great idea.

593
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:02,799
Don't forget, we've still got to
sort Eddie out as well. Yes, we do.

594
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:05,319
I'm not apologising for
something I didn't do.

595
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:09,079
- No, of course not, no-one would
expect you to. - Sean had an idea.

596
00:37:09,080 --> 00:37:12,279
Mm, I mean, he wouldn't believe me
that it was Albert,

597
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:15,519
