I can convince him it was me.

598
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:17,119
What, you'd hold your hand up?

599
00:37:17,120 --> 00:37:21,119
Yeah, if that's what it takes to fix
it then that's what I have to do.

600
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:23,639
Well, I think that's brilliant,
Sean.

601
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:27,879
Yeah. Yeah, it is. Only thing is,
I'm not sure what to say to him.

602
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:30,879
- Just say sorry for scribbling
on his photo. - Yeah, that's fine.

603
00:37:30,880 --> 00:37:34,679
No, no, no, no, it was more
than that, it was Ian rush.

604
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:36,659
He's football royalty
for scousers.

605
00:37:36,660 --> 00:37:38,259
No, you've got to say
something like, erm...

606
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:40,639
I'm sorry for defacing the photograph

607
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,639
of the greatest footballer
who ever lived.

608
00:37:43,040 --> 00:37:44,359
Sounds a bit over the top.

609
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:45,999
Yeah, well he's obsessed,
I'm telling you.

610
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:47,799
What about the other thing, though?

611
00:37:47,999 --> 00:37:51,299
That he wants us to say that
liverpool is better than west ham?

612
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:53,719
No, no, that was just for Ash.

613
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:55,879
I don't even support west ham.

614
00:37:55,880 --> 00:38:00,679
- They were relegated! - Oi, they
weren't relegated in that way.

615
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:02,119
So how many ways are there?

616
00:38:02,120 --> 00:38:04,719
That's what a lot of people think,
you see, that west ham went down

617
00:38:04,820 --> 00:38:06,639
because they weren't any good,
but that's not true.

618
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:09,739
No, no, we just went in the
championship for a rest, right?

619
00:38:09,740 --> 00:38:14,139
To take a break before we launched
our next assault on the premiership.

620
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:19,639
- So should I say it or not?
- Well, Eddie is stubborn remember.

621
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:22,458
Just tell him that liverpool are
the greatest team on the planet.

622
00:38:22,459 --> 00:38:24,359
Yes, he would
definitely go for that.

623
00:38:24,360 --> 00:38:26,179
And when he's gone for
that and shaken hands,

624
00:38:26,180 --> 00:38:29,379
- give him a message from Ash.
- Yeah? What's that?

625
00:38:29,380 --> 00:38:31,419
That liverpool play like bunch
of girls and west ham

626
00:38:31,420 --> 00:38:32,818
are the only proper
team in Europe.

627
00:38:33,019 --> 00:38:34,019
That's not going to help.

628
00:38:34,020 --> 00:38:35,459
It is true, honestly.

629
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:40,679
All right... Sean, it is
very kind of you to do this,

630
00:38:40,680 --> 00:38:41,839
but let's move on.

631
00:38:42,540 --> 00:38:44,898
Tomorrow, at nine,
Emma sets up the mark.

632
00:38:44,899 --> 00:38:47,199
Ash, make sure
the bars are in place.

633
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:50,738
And remember, we need
to make sure this guy believes

634
00:38:50,739 --> 00:38:52,539
that this is just a deal
that's gone wrong,

635
00:38:52,540 --> 00:38:54,719
not that he's been conned.
Ok?

636
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:56,760
So Albert and I will work out
a way of blowing him out clean.

637
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:04,320
Meet you at my car.
I'll see you there.

638
00:39:32,960 --> 00:39:35,160
You all right?

639
00:39:41,320 --> 00:39:42,920
Well?

640
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:45,399
I assume it all checked out.

641
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:47,519
Good as gold.

642
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:49,679
So we have a deal?

643
00:39:49,680 --> 00:39:50,679
When and where?

644
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:52,560
Under the motorway,
same as last time.

645
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:56,200
One hour.

646
00:39:57,440 --> 00:40:00,360
- You'd better get on to your buyer.
- All right.

647
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:06,239
Shania!

648
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:08,280
Get Heinz on the phone. Now!

649
00:40:11,720 --> 00:40:13,319
(Phone rings)

650
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:16,119
Heinz!
Happy days, we're on.

651
00:40:16,120 --> 00:40:19,039
Barry will bring you to the meeting
point, stick behind us in my car.

652
00:40:19,240 --> 00:40:21,180
I'll be there.
Bring your cheque book.

653
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:43,800
All right?

654
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:51,839
You ready? Oh, yeah.
Well, let's get on with it then.

655
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:55,960
Unless you want a 50-strong special ops
unit dropping in to spoil the party.

656
00:41:01,840 --> 00:41:04,279
He's setting us up!

657
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:07,959
Whoa! Whoa! No!
No, they're with me!

658
00:41:07,960 --> 00:41:09,400
No! It's all right!
It's all good!

659
00:41:09,401 --> 00:41:12,359
It's good as gold. No, see,
they're with me.

660
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:14,399
That's my lad, Barry.

661
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:17,719
He's brought my buyer. See,
I'm the middle man, he's the buyer.

662
00:41:17,720 --> 00:41:21,480
He pays me, I pay you,
that's how it works. Ok?

663
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:32,319
- What do you need?
- See the gold.

664
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:34,400
Er, we need to see the goods.

665
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:37,200
Sir?

666
00:41:44,640 --> 00:41:46,320
You'll like this, Heinz.

667
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:49,760
I verified the gold.

668
00:41:58,840 --> 00:42:01,280
See?
Everyone's happy!

669
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:04,079
It's all good.

670
00:42:04,080 --> 00:42:06,799
It's just business, that's all.

671
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:09,959
Freeze! Yo, back up!
Tell him to back up!

672
00:42:09,960 --> 00:42:13,400
It's ok! I'm going
to pay you now.

673
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:02,160
(He chuckles)

674
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:06,200
(Rumbling sound)

675
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:34,560
They're on to us!

676
00:44:00,360 --> 00:44:03,159
You nearly got us bloody killed.

677
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:06,159
I hope our next delivery
is not quite so eventful.

678
00:44:06,160 --> 00:44:09,319
Yeah, sorry about that, Heinz.
But all's well and all that, yeah?

679
00:44:09,320 --> 00:44:10,799
Chin up!

680
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:12,240
Auf wiedersehen!

681
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:16,618
Right. Get back to the office,
see how them ads are doing.

682
00:44:16,619 --> 00:44:17,819
Can't I come back with you?

683
00:44:17,820 --> 00:44:20,960
No you can't, I've got things to do.
Look, there's a bus stop over there.

684
00:44:30,640 --> 00:44:32,959
Sorry, sir. Closed.

685
00:44:32,960 --> 00:44:36,039
What do you mean it's closed?
It's one o'clock!

686
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:37,499
I've got a bankers' draft to cash.

687
00:44:37,500 --> 00:44:40,899
- The bank ceased trading at
11.30 this morning, sir. - What!?

688
00:44:40,900 --> 00:44:42,799
I'm not sure of the details,
sir, but the bank's assets

689
00:44:42,800 --> 00:44:44,599
