know they did archery there.

699
00:45:20,680 --> 00:45:22,479
He said it would've
been all right, though.

700
00:45:22,480 --> 00:45:24,679
Excuse me for just a moment.

701
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:26,359
Sure.
Sorry.

702
00:45:26,360 --> 00:45:28,879
You talked the talk,
it's time to walk the walk.

703
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:30,799
There's three mill's worth here,
are you in or are you out?

704
00:45:30,800 --> 00:45:32,799
Ok, we have a deal.

705
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:33,799
I'll take them all.

706
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:35,559
Good call.
Be in touch.

707
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:39,399
I can do the paperwork,
but can you handle it?

708
00:45:39,400 --> 00:45:42,039
You've talked the talk,
it's time to walk the walk.

709
00:45:42,040 --> 00:45:44,480
There's three mill's worth
here, are you in or out?

710
00:45:45,800 --> 00:45:48,439
Ok, we have a deal.

711
00:45:48,440 --> 00:45:51,639
- I'll take them all.
- Good call.

712
00:45:51,640 --> 00:45:53,919
Be in touch.

713
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:56,440
As brilliant as ever you were.

714
00:45:58,480 --> 00:46:00,199
Thank you, Paul.

715
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:02,039
Shania!

716
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:05,400
Get Heinz on the phone. Now!

717
00:46:08,240 --> 00:46:09,839
(Phone rings)

718
00:46:09,840 --> 00:46:11,119
Mm-hmm.

719
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:13,279
'Heinz! Happy days!

720
00:46:13,280 --> 00:46:14,719
'We're on!'

721
00:46:14,720 --> 00:46:16,280
I'll be there.

722
00:46:26,280 --> 00:46:29,360
It's all good.
See? Everyone's happy!

723
00:46:52,560 --> 00:46:54,520
I'd better get this
melted back down.

724
00:46:54,521 --> 00:46:56,239
Ah, but... not this one.

725
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:58,520
You, eh...
You sure that's the right one?

726
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:01,239
Thank you.

727
00:47:01,240 --> 00:47:02,759
For you guys, any time.

728
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:05,240
I knew you were good
but getting the army onside?

729
00:47:05,241 --> 00:47:06,560
How did that work?

730
00:47:08,360 --> 00:47:10,799
Can I ask why you're selling?

731
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:13,039
There's an army base
half a mile away,

732
00:47:13,040 --> 00:47:15,879
they're meant to do their
manoeuvres in the next field.

733
00:47:15,880 --> 00:47:18,519
But they keep getting lost
and ending up on my farm.

734
00:47:18,520 --> 00:47:21,719
Every Tuesday and Saturday at noon.
Just like clockwork.

735
00:47:21,720 --> 00:47:22,880
(Alarm bleeps)

736
00:47:28,040 --> 00:47:29,559
Trade secret.

737
00:47:29,560 --> 00:47:31,919
We could tell you
but we'd have to kill you.

738
00:47:31,920 --> 00:47:33,400
Fair enough.

739
00:47:38,560 --> 00:47:40,920
We had to change the seal
but it's all there.

740
00:47:52,040 --> 00:47:55,199
- It's done. - All right?
- Let's get rid of Heinz's phone.

741
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:56,600
Hi.
This is for you.

742
00:48:01,640 --> 00:48:04,279
(Phone rings)

743
00:48:04,280 --> 00:48:06,199
Hello?

744
00:48:06,200 --> 00:48:08,720
Your cheque's no good!
You nicked my gold!

745
00:48:09,960 --> 00:48:11,039
Who is that?

746
00:48:11,040 --> 00:48:13,159
It's Norman.

747
00:48:13,160 --> 00:48:15,280
'Cock-a-doodle-doo.'

748
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:18,200
'hello?'

749
00:48:19,200 --> 00:48:20,279
'hello?'

750
00:48:20,280 --> 00:48:21,640
'hello!'

751
00:48:22,600 --> 00:48:23,640
'hello?!'

752
00:48:34,480 --> 00:48:35,879
so Eddie's all sorted?

753
00:48:35,880 --> 00:48:37,639
Like it never happened.

754
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:41,239
So what, you apologised, bigged up
liverpool and he swallowed it?

755
00:48:41,240 --> 00:48:43,199
Yeah.

756
00:48:43,200 --> 00:48:44,799
He didn't mention my name?

757
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:47,759
Let's just say it's forgotten.

758
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:49,519
Just like that?

759
00:48:49,520 --> 00:48:52,239
I had to use charm, talk him round.
But yeah, he's sweet.

760
00:48:52,240 --> 00:48:53,959
So we can go back in?

761
00:48:53,960 --> 00:48:56,319
- Whenever we like.
- Well done, Sean.

762
00:48:56,320 --> 00:48:58,040
- Absolutely.
- Thank you.

763
00:49:01,000 --> 00:49:02,360
(Woman sobs)

764
00:49:04,880 --> 00:49:06,879
So what did you
say to him exactly?

765
00:49:06,880 --> 00:49:08,519
Well...

766
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:11,199
- It was Ash.
- Knew it!

767
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:13,519
So where is he then?

768
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:15,480
Come on, you know him.
He's a proud man.

769
00:49:15,481 --> 00:49:17,799
I want an apology.
And he wants to apologise.

770
00:49:17,800 --> 00:49:20,640
He just can't bring himself
to do it face-to-face.

771
00:49:21,840 --> 00:49:23,040
So he gave me this.

772
00:49:33,240 --> 00:49:34,639
'A message from Ash.

773
00:49:34,640 --> 00:49:36,639
'I'm sorry for defacing
the photograph

774
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:39,499
'of the greatest footballer
who ever lived. Ian rush.'

775
00:49:39,500 --> 00:49:42,618
guys, what a lot of people think
west ham went down cos

776
00:49:42,619 --> 00:49:44,519
they weren't any good
but that's not true.

777
00:49:44,520 --> 00:49:47,719
No, no. We just went into the
championship for a rest, right,

778
00:49:47,720 --> 00:49:52,120
to take a break before we launched
our next assault on the premiership.

779
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:56,040
So should I say it or not?

780
00:49:56,041 --> 00:49:58,599
Tell him liverpool
are the best team on the planet.

781
00:49:58,600 --> 00:50:00,399
He would definitely go for that.

782
00:50:00,400 --> 00:50:03,279
When he's gone for that and you've
shaken hands, give him a message.

783
00:50:03,280 --> 00:50:04,639
Yeah?
What's that?

784
00:50:04,640 --> 00:50:06,320
Liverpool play like a bunch
of girls and west ham

785
00:50:06,359 --> 00:50:07,559
are the only proper team in Europe.

786
00:50:12,360 --> 00:50:15,039
'Liverpool are the only
proper team in Europe.'

787
00:50:15,040 --> 00:50:16,559
(brilliant!)

788
00:50:16,560 --> 00:50:20,759
'Let's be honest. West ham went down
because they weren't good enough.

789
00:50:20,760 --> 00:50:22,879
'Liverpool are the best team
on the planet.

790
00:50:22,880 --> 00:50:24,640
'West ham play like a load of girls

791
00:50:24,641 --> 00:50:27,240
'and liverpool are the only
proper team in Europe.'

792
00:50:28,520 --> 00:50:29,559
so we're good?

793
00:50:29,560 --> 00:50:31,080
Come here.

794
00:50:33,600 --> 00:50:36,080
I pretty much told him
exactly what you told me to.

795
00:50:36,081 --> 00:50:39,479
I mean, I might not have got it
word for word, but you know.

796
00:50:39,480 --> 00:50:41,840
But you gave him the gist?
Oh, yeah. Yeah, yeah.

797
00:50:45,360 --> 00:50:46,879
That is a very happy lady.

798
00:50:46,880 --> 00:50:48,240
So what did you tell her?

799
00:50:48,241 --> 00:50:52,559
I told her I was an ombudsman
and she'd just been awarded damages.

800
00:50:52,560 --> 00:50:54,439
A very sweet thing for you to do.

801
00:50:54,440 --> 00:50:56,879
Well, thank you all for your help.
Any time.

802
00:50:56,880 --> 00:50:59,159
And the good news is,
we can go back to Eddie's.

803
00:50:59,160 --> 00:51:02,639
Oh?
Yeah, Sean did the business.

804
00:51:02,640 --> 00:51:05,560
Well, what are we waiting for?

805
00:51:07,480 --> 00:51:10,399
Guys! Good to see you, come on in.

806
00:51:10,400 --> 00:51:12,999
So we're ok? Eh?

807
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:14,839
All forgotten,
not another word.

808
00:51:14,840 --> 00:51:17,599
Bottle of bubbly on ice,
waiting for you. On the house.

809
00:51:17,600 --> 00:51:18,959
Thank you, Eddie!

810
00:51:18,960 --> 00:51:20,280
Cheers, Eddie.
It's ok.

811
00:51:21,720 --> 00:51:22,760
Oh.

812
00:51:25,080 --> 00:51:26,120
All right, ed?

813
00:51:30,760 --> 00:51:33,080
You're a top man, Ash,
you know that?

814
00:51:35,200 --> 00:51:37,200
It's not easy
admitting you're wrong.

815
00:51:38,320 --> 00:51:40,599
No, no, it can't have been.

816
00:51:40,600 --> 00:51:43,800
- Takes a big man to step up
to the plate. - Yes, it does.

817
00:51:44,800 --> 00:51:46,839
Any chance of you letting go now?

818
00:51:46,840 --> 00:51:48,440
Sorry.

819
00:51:49,680 --> 00:51:52,199
Look, I know
you don't like any fuss

820
00:51:52,200 --> 00:51:54,839
but I just want you to know, that...

821
00:51:54,840 --> 00:51:56,640
I respect you...As a man.

822
00:51:58,440 --> 00:52:00,799
And I respect you too, ed.

823
00:52:00,800 --> 00:52:02,159
As a man.

824
00:52:02,160 --> 00:52:04,239
I know you do. I know you do.

825
00:52:04,240 --> 00:52:08,680
So that's it then, yeah, water under
the bridge, not another word? Right.

826
00:52:09,760 --> 00:52:11,640
Right.

827
00:52:14,240 --> 00:52:16,319
Right, shall we open the bottle, or?

828
00:52:16,320 --> 00:52:17,519
Yes, yes.

829
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:19,079
(Mickey laughs)
Ok, now.

830
00:52:19,080 --> 00:52:24,440
This...ls to a golden future.

831
00:52:34,240 --> 00:52:36,439
Bet you never thought
you'd see me again.

832
00:52:36,440 --> 00:52:38,399
Back off, corporal.

833
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:40,239
No, we didn't.

834
00:52:40,240 --> 00:52:43,439
Only when you were taking me
into the barn, I heard you talking.

835
00:52:43,440 --> 00:52:45,320
Eddie's isn't the only bar
in London.

836
00:52:47,120 --> 00:52:49,839
Maybe we should just find
somewhere else.

837
00:52:49,840 --> 00:52:51,760
No, no,
we'll find a way to sort it.

838
00:52:53,680 --> 00:52:55,440
It was a bit of a long shot, but...

839
00:52:56,840 --> 00:53:00,040
Tell you the truth, I thought
you'd be long gone by now.

840
00:53:01,760 --> 00:53:03,280
The thing is...

841
00:53:04,680 --> 00:53:08,760
..That half a million quid broke me
and someone's got to pay.

842
00:53:10,280 --> 00:53:14,239
So...What do you have in mind?

843
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:15,600
Ash: Relax.

844
00:53:19,320 --> 00:53:22,040
Look, I haven't got any beef
with you guys.

845
00:53:23,520 --> 00:53:24,799
Sorry?

846
00:53:24,800 --> 00:53:28,399
Ok, you got my money, but that was
business. I understand that.

847
00:53:28,400 --> 00:53:31,840
I got the gold,
I gave it to Heinz, I took a hit.

848
00:53:33,200 --> 00:53:36,920
You kept to your end of the bargain,
I've got no complaints about that.

849
00:53:38,440 --> 00:53:41,080
But that kraut cheated me!

850
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:46,320
He took my gold and he gave me a
dodgy cheque, now I can't find him.

851
00:53:47,520 --> 00:53:49,839
His office number's unavailable

852
00:53:49,840 --> 00:53:51,920
and some nutcase
has nicked his mobile.

853
00:53:58,600 --> 00:53:59,840
50 grand.

854
00:54:06,600 --> 00:54:09,039
Now, I know you lot
were black ops in the army,

855
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:12,240
so I thought who better
to help me out.

856
00:54:13,240 --> 00:54:14,319
Black ops?

857
00:54:14,320 --> 00:54:17,520
It's ok.
I know you can't talk about it.

858
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:20,679
But I know how it works.

859
00:54:20,680 --> 00:54:22,479
I know what you do.

860
00:54:22,480 --> 00:54:23,920
What's that, then?

861
00:54:25,960 --> 00:54:28,919
You get dropped behind enemy lines
to take people out.

862
00:54:28,920 --> 00:54:32,839
Well, that's what I want you to do
to the German.

863
00:54:32,840 --> 00:54:34,680
I want you to track him down for me.

864
00:54:34,681 --> 00:54:36,999
His name is Heinz Zimmerman.

865
00:54:37,000 --> 00:54:38,799
I want you to find him,

866
00:54:38,800 --> 00:54:41,319
and I want you to...
Take care of him for me.

867
00:54:41,320 --> 00:54:43,359
"Take care of him?"
You know what I mean.

868
00:54:43,360 --> 00:54:45,400
Oh, yeah. Take care of him.

869
00:54:46,400 --> 00:54:49,719
There's 50 grand there,
there'll be the same again

870
00:54:49,720 --> 00:54:51,360
when you bring him to me.

871
00:54:52,440 --> 00:54:57,560
Or show me a photo...
Of his cold, dead body.

872
00:55:06,200 --> 00:55:07,240
Do we have a deal?

873
00:55:07,241 --> 00:55:09,480
Let me get this straight.

874
00:55:10,840 --> 00:55:15,079
If we find this Heinz Zimmerman,
take care of him,

875
00:55:15,080 --> 00:55:19,800
and show you a photo of that,
you'll give us another 50 thousand?

876
00:55:21,160 --> 00:55:23,160
That's right.

877
00:55:29,720 --> 00:55:31,520
Then you've got a deal.

878
00:55:34,960 --> 00:55:36,560
You know where to find me.

879
00:55:46,840 --> 00:55:48,000
Did that just happen?

880
00:55:50,920 --> 00:55:54,039
Yes, it did. I thought we were
in trouble for a minute.

881
00:55:54,040 --> 00:55:57,080
Not to worry, I'm on it.

882
00:56:12,520 --> 00:56:13,960
Wait a minute.

883
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:18,839
Ugh, did you have to put ketchup
on this shirt?

884
00:56:18,840 --> 00:56:22,279
With five grand, you can buy a new
shirt. You have to look the part.

885
00:56:22,280 --> 00:56:23,840
Or dead to be precise.

886
00:56:25,000 --> 00:56:27,199
Ok, now, that. No.
Hold that, hold that.

887
00:56:27,200 --> 00:56:29,839
That's fantastic.

888
00:56:29,840 --> 00:56:31,599
I really missed you lot, you know.

889
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:33,679
Yeah, well, we missed you too, ed.

890
00:56:33,680 --> 00:56:36,000
Did you?
Yeah. Just don't hug me again.

891
00:56:37,640 --> 00:56:39,239
Here's to west ham.

892
00:56:39,240 --> 00:56:41,200
Oh, cheers.

893
00:56:45,760 --> 00:56:48,440
Hang on a minute, you're supposed
to say, "here's to liverpool."

894
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:50,680
What for?

895
00:56:52,280 --> 00:56:53,999
Well, that's not very nice, is it?

896
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:57,159
What's the point in apologising
if you behave like that?

897
00:56:57,160 --> 00:56:59,439
But Sean apologised, I didn't.

898
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:01,999
Yes, you did.
No, I didn't do anything.

899
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:03,040
What about the cd?

900
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:06,640
What cd?

901
00:57:10,160 --> 00:57:11,320
'Message from Ash.

902
00:57:11,321 --> 00:57:13,359
'I'm sorry for defacing
the photograph

903
00:57:13,360 --> 00:57:16,599
'of the greatest footballer
who ever lived. Ian rush.'

904
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:17,639
Ash...

905
00:57:17,640 --> 00:57:19,239
This...

906
00:57:19,240 --> 00:57:21,320
This can be easily explained.

907
00:57:22,360 --> 00:57:24,720
How about two dead bodies
for the price of one.

908
00:57:26,000 --> 00:57:27,760
Only one of 'em will be real...

909
00:57:28,960 --> 00:57:30,360
..Cos I'm going to kill you.

910
00:57:30,361 --> 00:57:31,839
Ash. Sean, just run.

911
00:57:31,840 --> 00:57:34,239
Don't just stand there! Help me!

912
00:57:34,240 --> 00:57:36,999
